WEBVTT

00:00.895 --> 00:02.664
<i>Previously on "Midnight, Texas"...</i>

00:02.686 --> 00:05.218
<i>I was an angel. I'm fallen.</i>

00:05.248 --> 00:07.476
<i>The veil that Midnight
sits upon, it's fraying.</i>

00:07.505 --> 00:09.093
I'm speaking to you as a friend.

00:09.125 --> 00:10.974
And a reverend who
will keep your secret.

00:11.008 --> 00:12.142
You don't know, do you?

00:12.176 --> 00:13.510
Mr. All-American here,

00:13.544 --> 00:14.711
he was once one of us.

00:14.745 --> 00:16.312
<i>I was 17.</i>

00:16.347 --> 00:18.148
- I was ashamed.
- I need time.

00:18.182 --> 00:19.548
You ever think about leaving Midnight?

00:19.550 --> 00:21.940
I'm not leaving my brother here alone

00:21.979 --> 00:23.320
with my dad. You know that.

00:23.354 --> 00:26.089
I know her. That's
Aubrey. Aubrey Hamilton.

00:26.123 --> 00:27.542
<i>The killer is still out there.</i>

00:27.565 --> 00:29.792
<i>You really want to find
him, you keep looking.</i>

00:29.794 --> 00:31.728
[SHRIEKS]

00:31.762 --> 00:33.663
<i>[UPBEAT ROCK MUSIC]</i>

00:33.698 --> 00:35.862
Calling all freaks and geeks here

00:35.893 --> 00:37.400
for the Midnighters' show!

00:37.435 --> 00:38.990
- Full moon rising.
- Hey, guys, maybe

00:39.006 --> 00:40.370
- we shouldn't be so loud.
- Why?

00:40.404 --> 00:41.579
Are you afraid they're gonna get you?

00:41.581 --> 00:43.701
- They who?
- For one, the werewolves.

00:43.733 --> 00:47.610
[MEN HOWLING, CHUCKLING]

00:47.645 --> 00:50.113
[GRUNTING]

00:50.147 --> 00:51.780
Hey, hey, let's go check
out that greenhouse.

00:51.782 --> 00:53.515
Could be that witch is
growing some dank weed...

00:53.517 --> 00:55.418
Excuse me?

00:55.453 --> 00:57.053
[ENERGY WHOOSHES]

00:57.088 --> 01:00.256
- [WIND WHISTLING]
- Agh!

01:00.291 --> 01:01.391
[CHUCKLES]

01:01.425 --> 01:03.059
Now scat.

01:03.094 --> 01:04.426
We're gonna burn you at the stake,

01:04.428 --> 01:06.463
Sabrina the middle-aged bitch!

01:06.497 --> 01:09.466
I am not middle-aged.

01:09.500 --> 01:14.471
<i>♪</i>

01:14.505 --> 01:15.638
[SPRAY CAN RATTLING]

01:15.673 --> 01:18.641
<i>[EERIE MUSIC]</i>

01:18.676 --> 01:20.577
Cherry-popping time, Aerin.

01:20.611 --> 01:23.279
You know, it's okay. You go ahead.

01:23.314 --> 01:26.383
This place kind of creeps me out.

01:26.417 --> 01:30.286
[SPRAY PAINT HISSING]

01:35.459 --> 01:39.562
[SPRAY PAINT HISSING]

01:39.597 --> 01:42.065
- [SCREAMS]
- Boo!

01:42.099 --> 01:43.600
[LAUGHING]

01:43.634 --> 01:45.163
Hey, come on, let's jet.

01:47.271 --> 01:49.339
[METAL CHAINS CLANGING]

01:49.373 --> 01:53.243
[BESTIAL ROARING]

01:53.277 --> 01:55.078
Yo, I heard that they have parties here

01:55.112 --> 01:56.579
where they drink each other's blood

01:56.614 --> 01:58.181
and feast on the hearts of children.

01:58.215 --> 02:00.417
Sounds delectable.

02:00.451 --> 02:01.851
Is that why you're here?

02:01.886 --> 02:05.255
Because I'm feeling a little hungry.

02:05.289 --> 02:07.624
- Hurry up, man, let's go!
- Come on!

02:07.658 --> 02:11.294
Ryan, Ryan! Stop, please, wait for me!

02:11.328 --> 02:15.698
Ryan, wait! Ryan, please, wait for me!

02:15.733 --> 02:22.705
<i>♪</i>

02:22.740 --> 02:24.507
[WOLF HOWLS]

02:24.542 --> 02:27.678
Ryan, that was... No,
please, just come back,

02:27.710 --> 02:31.781
and we can... There you are.

02:31.816 --> 02:34.150
[ENGINE REVS]

02:34.185 --> 02:37.153
<i>[OMINOUS MUSIC]</i>

02:37.188 --> 02:43.560
<i>♪</i>

02:43.594 --> 02:45.295
[TIRES SQUEALING]

02:45.329 --> 02:51.434
<i>♪</i>

02:53.254 --> 02:54.904
[YELLS]

02:54.939 --> 02:57.640
[GASPS, SOBS]

02:57.675 --> 03:01.244
No, please, stop.

03:01.278 --> 03:02.879
[SOBBING]

03:02.913 --> 03:04.581
<i>♪</i>

03:04.615 --> 03:08.184
[WHIMPERING]

03:08.219 --> 03:10.386
<i>[SCREAMS]</i>

03:10.421 --> 03:17.393
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

03:17.428 --> 03:20.396
<i>[SOFT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]</i>

03:20.431 --> 03:27.537
<i>♪</i>

03:32.710 --> 03:36.379
<i>[OMINOUS MUSIC]</i>

03:36.413 --> 03:39.182
- [GROWLING] Fiji...
- [SCREAMS]

03:39.216 --> 03:41.851
[COUGHING]

03:41.886 --> 03:44.754
<i>♪</i>

03:44.788 --> 03:47.390
[SIGHS] It was just a nightmare.

03:47.424 --> 03:50.393
<i>[OMINOUS MUSIC]</i>

03:50.427 --> 03:57.534
<i>♪</i>

04:02.239 --> 04:04.274
[EXCLAIMS]

04:08.345 --> 04:12.315
[SIGHS] It's nice...

04:12.349 --> 04:16.486
You not having to sneak
off in the morning.

04:16.519 --> 04:18.522
I could get used to this.

04:26.931 --> 04:29.265
<i>[EERIE MUSIC]</i>

04:29.300 --> 04:32.402
[WOOD CREAKING]

04:32.436 --> 04:34.904
What? Are you not in the mood?

04:34.939 --> 04:40.577
Not that, I just... I got a headache.

04:40.611 --> 04:42.512
You get a lot of headaches.

04:42.546 --> 04:45.582
Lately, yeah.

04:45.616 --> 04:47.483
Well, maybe you ought to see a doctor.

04:47.518 --> 04:50.420
[SIGHS] It's not about my health.

04:50.454 --> 04:51.921
It's about me being a medium.

04:51.956 --> 04:55.425
When I see ghosts, spirits,

04:55.459 --> 04:58.618
it can make me feel, like, sick,

04:58.661 --> 05:00.795
like a hangover.

05:00.798 --> 05:04.434
The more I see, the worse the hangover.

05:04.468 --> 05:07.370
Lately, I've been seeing a lot.

05:07.404 --> 05:10.340
I do know a foolproof hangover remedy.

05:12.009 --> 05:15.778
<i>[MUFFLED SHRIEKS, EERIE TONES]</i>

05:19.984 --> 05:22.952
<i>[LIVELY MUSIC PLAYING OVER RADIO]</i>

05:22.987 --> 05:30.026
<i>♪</i>

05:32.363 --> 05:34.063
Good morning, Manfred.

05:34.098 --> 05:35.465
How was your night?

05:35.499 --> 05:38.635
Good, and yours?

05:38.669 --> 05:42.905
Mine wasn't great either.

05:42.940 --> 05:44.707
Yeah, full moon last night.

05:48.879 --> 05:53.650
My wereself... it's hungry.

05:53.684 --> 05:56.886
Every day, I see more and more spirits.

05:56.920 --> 05:59.889
Feels like something weird is going on.

06:01.759 --> 06:04.360
Wow, you're alive. I started to doubt it

06:04.395 --> 06:06.496
'cause you never answer any of my texts.

06:06.530 --> 06:09.432
I've been busy covering
your shifts at the Gas & Go.

06:09.466 --> 06:11.734
That's on Dad. He did
not have to fire me.

06:11.769 --> 06:13.670
How's it going with you and Dad?

06:13.704 --> 06:15.438
You announced that you're hooking up

06:15.472 --> 06:17.573
with the town con man.

06:17.608 --> 06:19.008
Guess how it's going.

06:19.043 --> 06:20.777
I'm not gonna apologize for what I did.

06:20.811 --> 06:22.679
Fine, don't apologize,

06:22.713 --> 06:25.081
but don't expect me
to be excited about it.

06:25.115 --> 06:27.684
Thanks. See ya.

06:27.718 --> 06:31.688
Whoa, whoa, what happened?

06:31.722 --> 06:34.524
It's not important.

06:34.558 --> 06:35.992
Did Dad do that?

06:38.154 --> 06:42.557
You left. So please, just...

06:42.599 --> 06:44.734
Just leave it alone.

06:48.906 --> 06:51.541
Excuse me?

06:51.575 --> 06:55.878
My friend was in here
last night... uh, Aerin.

06:58.115 --> 07:00.783
Her mom called and said
that she didn't make it home,

07:00.818 --> 07:02.874
and, uh, have you seen her?

07:02.898 --> 07:05.054
We're pretty worried about her.

07:05.089 --> 07:08.491
- I'm sorry, no.
- Neither did I.

07:08.525 --> 07:12.729
However, I did see my
cemetery was vandalized.

07:12.763 --> 07:17.767
You weren't here with
your friend, were you?

07:17.801 --> 07:22.071
Uh, no, no, I... I don't
know anything about that.

07:22.106 --> 07:24.700
Maybe my friend Manfred here could help.

07:24.731 --> 07:27.176
He's... intuitive.

07:27.211 --> 07:28.945
No, stop, stop right there.

07:28.979 --> 07:32.081
Don't use that witchy crap on me.

07:32.116 --> 07:34.684
It was a mistake asking you people.

07:34.718 --> 07:37.920
- "You people"?
- He's inconsequential.

07:37.955 --> 07:41.591
What is a problem is that
there's another missing girl.

07:42.559 --> 07:45.595
Hopefully she's just out partying.

07:45.629 --> 07:47.494
Yeah, and not laying
in a ditch somewhere.

07:47.502 --> 07:50.133
Still, we should try and find her.

07:50.167 --> 07:53.770
What if something else is going on?

07:53.804 --> 07:57.106
Something supernatural?

07:57.141 --> 07:59.842
Manfred, you've been seeing
an uptick in ghosts, right?

07:59.877 --> 08:03.088
Seeing and hearing, everywhere.

08:03.104 --> 08:04.647
Psychic energy's off the charts.

08:04.681 --> 08:06.248
And I've been finding
dead animals and bugs

08:06.250 --> 08:07.683
on Witch Light Road.

08:07.718 --> 08:09.619
Shouldn't we focus on finding the girl?

08:09.653 --> 08:11.687
I'm gonna head out to the ranches.

08:11.722 --> 08:13.723
Creek and I'll take the back woods.

08:13.757 --> 08:17.727
<i>♪</i>

08:17.761 --> 08:20.129
Bobo, you're with me.

08:20.164 --> 08:24.066
Rev, you and I can look in town.

08:24.101 --> 08:26.135
Don't look too excited.

08:26.170 --> 08:30.506
<i>♪</i>

08:30.541 --> 08:33.743
You've known me a long time and, uh...

08:33.777 --> 08:39.015
I've always been optimistic,

08:39.049 --> 08:41.551
able to see the light in the darkness.

08:41.585 --> 08:43.553
And you have a flair for prints.

08:43.587 --> 08:46.656
[CHUCKLES] Well, thank you.

08:48.559 --> 08:51.060
Lately, um...

08:51.094 --> 08:53.930
I've been failing.

08:53.964 --> 08:57.867
It's... it's been hard.

09:00.704 --> 09:02.605
I haven't been sleeping.

09:02.639 --> 09:04.941
<i>♪</i>

09:04.975 --> 09:08.544
I hear this voice...

09:08.579 --> 09:11.280
calling me.

09:11.315 --> 09:14.684
I feel something touching me.

09:14.718 --> 09:17.253
And I have this terrible
feeling that it's not gonna stop

09:17.285 --> 09:18.621
until it takes me.

09:18.655 --> 09:20.122
You were just kidnapped.

09:20.157 --> 09:22.024
It's natural that
you'd feel a bit shaken.

09:22.059 --> 09:23.793
It's not that.

09:23.827 --> 09:25.595
<i>♪</i>

09:25.629 --> 09:27.763
I feel like a demon is after me.

09:27.798 --> 09:30.933
<i>♪</i>

09:30.968 --> 09:33.135
Or I'm going crazy. [LAUGHS]

09:33.170 --> 09:35.071
<i>♪</i>

09:35.105 --> 09:37.106
You're not going crazy.

09:37.140 --> 09:43.713
<i>♪</i>

09:43.747 --> 09:45.982
Are these trees all
beginning to look the same?

09:46.016 --> 09:48.885
It might look like it, but I
know these woods pretty well.

09:48.919 --> 09:50.720
Connor and I would explore for hours

09:50.754 --> 09:52.855
when we first moved to Midnight.

09:55.371 --> 09:58.373
I think my dad is taking out
his anger at me on Connor.

10:00.831 --> 10:02.932
I saw a bruise on Connor's arm.

10:04.701 --> 10:07.336
- Has he ever hit you?
- No.

10:07.371 --> 10:09.739
Even after Mom died,
as messed up as he was,

10:09.773 --> 10:11.173
he never laid a finger on us.

10:11.208 --> 10:12.742
<i>[MUFFLED WHIMPERING]</i>

10:12.776 --> 10:14.277
What is it?

10:14.311 --> 10:18.648
Oh, my God, is that her?

10:18.682 --> 10:20.349
[FLIES BUZZING]

10:20.384 --> 10:24.754
Uh, no, no, she's been here a while.

10:24.788 --> 10:26.622
It's another girl?

10:26.657 --> 10:27.957
Yeah.

10:31.061 --> 10:32.895
I think I've met her.

10:39.808 --> 10:42.909
[GRUNTING]

10:44.890 --> 10:49.226
If you're here, please
make yourself known.

10:49.261 --> 10:51.095
Her name's Tiffany.

10:51.129 --> 10:55.099
Right, Tiffany.

10:55.133 --> 10:59.270
We met on the vampire bus.
You were donating blood.

10:59.304 --> 11:01.205
She was killed a while ago.

11:01.239 --> 11:03.707
Yeah, a lot of things were killed here.

11:03.742 --> 11:05.609
Tell me what happened.

11:05.644 --> 11:07.778
We need to stop whoever did this to you.

11:07.812 --> 11:09.258
Oh, you poor thing,

11:09.274 --> 11:11.315
you were just dumped
out here like garbage.

11:11.349 --> 11:15.619
[SCOFFS] Yeah, she survived
a vampire bus for this.

11:15.654 --> 11:17.288
<i>♪</i>

11:17.322 --> 11:18.923
I'm not getting anything.

11:18.957 --> 11:22.461
Her spirit's not here. It moved on,

11:22.485 --> 11:25.663
which is a good thing,
the natural order.

11:25.697 --> 11:28.332
Spirits that stay are
unsettled, unhappy.

11:28.366 --> 11:30.935
- This is another Aubrey.
- We don't know that.

11:30.969 --> 11:33.137
Yeah, I do. Lowry didn't kill Aubrey.

11:33.171 --> 11:35.339
I know I didn't. Someone
else dragged her body

11:35.373 --> 11:37.241
to the river, left her here to die.

11:37.275 --> 11:39.176
Same person who did this.

11:39.211 --> 11:41.679
Should we call the authorities?

11:41.713 --> 11:43.747
In case someone is looking for her...

11:43.782 --> 11:48.152
No, Tiffany fell of the grid
long before she got to Midnight.

11:48.186 --> 11:50.980
We need to find who did this.

11:51.011 --> 11:54.158
- Deal with it ourselves.
- Which means what, exactly?

11:54.192 --> 11:55.826
We'll decide the punishment

11:55.860 --> 11:57.361
when we find out who's doing this.

11:57.395 --> 12:01.098
For now, let's just go
look for the other girl.

12:01.132 --> 12:03.734
Fingers crossed we find her
before the cops start digging.

12:04.869 --> 12:06.736
You sure you didn't see her?

12:06.766 --> 12:10.007
No, but then again, I
was down for the night

12:10.041 --> 12:12.592
- before sunset.
- Well, that's early.

12:12.599 --> 12:15.713
Midnight's a sleepy town.
I don't know why folks

12:15.747 --> 12:17.448
have to be so disrespectful.

12:17.482 --> 12:20.718
It wasn't that long ago
Aubrey Lowry went missing.

12:20.752 --> 12:22.486
Found her dead by the river.

12:22.520 --> 12:25.155
Killed by her husband,
as far as I understood.

12:27.259 --> 12:29.860
Still an open case until we find him.

12:29.894 --> 12:34.732
This girl, her mom's a judge
in Davy, and she's scared,

12:34.766 --> 12:37.301
so we told her we'd search around.

12:37.335 --> 12:41.005
But, in 24 hours, there's
gonna be a full investigation.

12:41.039 --> 12:44.208
<i>[OMINOUS MUSIC]</i>

12:44.242 --> 12:48.879
<i>♪</i>

12:48.913 --> 12:51.348
They here about the girl?

12:51.383 --> 12:56.353
No sign of her out by the ranches.

12:56.388 --> 13:01.258
Fiji thinks she's going mad
because she hears demons.

13:01.293 --> 13:03.327
Manfred is self-medicating
because he sees

13:03.361 --> 13:06.430
spirits everywhere.

13:06.464 --> 13:11.201
I promised to keep your
secret, but the others?

13:11.236 --> 13:14.338
They deserve to know
they're not going crazy.

13:14.372 --> 13:17.408
Nothing I say is gonna
stop what's coming.

13:17.442 --> 13:19.843
Eventually, they'll know everything.

13:19.878 --> 13:22.913
When? When demons start crawling

13:22.947 --> 13:25.282
- out of the veil?
- I am protecting my family.

13:25.317 --> 13:29.053
At the expense of everyone else?

13:29.087 --> 13:33.557
I know you sent Chuy away. Why?

13:33.591 --> 13:36.260
Because the veil is so
dangerous for him here?

13:36.294 --> 13:38.395
This is an impossible choice.

13:38.430 --> 13:41.098
I wanna help, but if
it gets out that there's

13:41.132 --> 13:43.367
a fallen angel here,
they will come for me,

13:43.401 --> 13:45.936
and, believe me, you do
not want that in Midnight.

13:45.970 --> 13:48.539
But what I can do is
keep looking for the girl.

13:48.573 --> 13:50.541
That's what I can do to help.

13:50.575 --> 13:53.277
<i>♪</i>

13:53.311 --> 13:54.603
<i>It's pissing me off.</i>

13:54.634 --> 13:55.954
I can't figure out

13:55.971 --> 13:57.638
if the killer's human or supernatural.

13:57.650 --> 13:59.450
Does it make a difference?

13:59.484 --> 14:01.243
Not to the victims.

14:01.275 --> 14:05.089
Look, Lem's vampire buds said
they felt Midnight call to them.

14:05.123 --> 14:06.957
Succubus pretty much said the same.

14:06.991 --> 14:08.858
It feels like every day
we're dealing with a different

14:08.860 --> 14:11.895
supernatural coming
to town, making noise.

14:11.930 --> 14:15.032
- Men can be just as evil.
- If not worse.

14:17.102 --> 14:21.972
- You talk to Fiji?
- I talk to Fiji all the time.

14:22.006 --> 14:24.975
She hate me?

14:25.009 --> 14:27.311
No, no.

14:27.345 --> 14:29.179
She thought you were perfect.

14:29.214 --> 14:32.282
- She put you on a pedestal.
- And I fell off.

14:32.317 --> 14:34.551
Well, hey, there's nowhere to go but up.

14:37.155 --> 14:42.025
Look, she knows what I do for a living.

14:42.060 --> 14:44.628
She doesn't like it...

14:44.662 --> 14:48.031
She doesn't judge.

14:48.066 --> 14:51.201
So don't sweat it. Still hope.

14:55.206 --> 14:57.174
So you just wanna check on Connor?

14:57.208 --> 15:00.644
I just wanna let him
know what's going on.

15:00.678 --> 15:04.314
Connor, you here?

15:04.349 --> 15:06.517
He'd call you if something was wrong.

15:06.551 --> 15:09.052
Yeah, or he'd keep
quiet and protect my dad.

15:09.087 --> 15:11.655
It's the Lovell way.
I'm gonna check out back.

15:13.525 --> 15:17.361
<i>[FAINT SCREECHING, EERIE CHATTERING]</i>

15:17.395 --> 15:23.333
<i>♪</i>

15:23.368 --> 15:27.504
<i>[EERIE, MUFFLED NOISES]</i>

15:27.539 --> 15:31.642
<i>♪</i>

15:31.676 --> 15:34.344
<i>[DISTANT SCREAMING]</i>

15:34.379 --> 15:37.414
Oh, great. You.

15:37.449 --> 15:38.916
What are you doing here?

15:38.950 --> 15:41.585
Mr. Lovell, I'm here with Creek.

15:41.619 --> 15:43.636
- Where is she?
- [SNIFFS]

15:43.652 --> 15:45.189
Starting early, huh?

15:47.025 --> 15:49.226
[GROANING] You come in my house,

15:49.260 --> 15:51.395
and I'm supposed to
explain myself to you?

15:51.429 --> 15:54.331
Are you kidding me?
You're hitting him now?

15:54.365 --> 15:56.934
- You okay?
- I'm fine, yeah.

15:56.968 --> 15:59.970
- We're looking for Connor.
- Well, he's not here.

16:01.372 --> 16:02.932
Just because I'm not here all the time

16:02.941 --> 16:04.474
doesn't mean I'm not
watching out for him.

16:04.476 --> 16:07.010
Get him out of my house.

16:07.045 --> 16:14.151
<i>♪</i>

16:16.087 --> 16:17.654
[SNIFFS]

16:20.391 --> 16:21.425
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

16:21.459 --> 16:22.626
There, I texted Connor.

16:22.660 --> 16:24.461
Warned him Dad's hammered.

16:24.496 --> 16:26.930
- What are you thinking?
- I'm thinking

16:26.965 --> 16:29.199
I should've kept lying.
I thought he could handle

16:29.234 --> 16:31.134
me having a life, but, boy, was I wrong.

16:31.169 --> 16:33.704
- Any luck?
- No, we searched the river,

16:33.738 --> 16:35.372
fields by the Gas & Go... No luck.

16:35.406 --> 16:37.074
Fiji and I searched the town.

16:37.108 --> 16:39.042
Well, should we check the road to Davy?

16:39.077 --> 16:40.743
Hey, I'm seeing a lot
of ghosts these days,

16:40.745 --> 16:45.082
so I'm not sure, but...
Is someone out there?

16:45.116 --> 16:47.618
<i>[OMINOUS MUSIC]</i>

16:47.652 --> 16:49.553
Connor!

16:49.587 --> 16:53.590
<i>♪</i>

16:53.625 --> 16:55.526
Oh, my God, what happened?

17:01.065 --> 17:04.433
He's disoriented, might be a concussion.

17:06.228 --> 17:08.194
Can I get you anything else?

17:11.074 --> 17:13.075
Connor...

17:15.670 --> 17:20.741
Um, you remember anything
about the person who did this?

17:20.775 --> 17:23.176
I... I went looking
for the missing girl,

17:23.211 --> 17:28.048
and someone hit me from behind.

17:28.083 --> 17:29.683
Same thing that happened to Aubrey.

17:29.718 --> 17:31.352
<i>♪</i>

17:31.386 --> 17:33.187
Are you sure it was human?

17:33.221 --> 17:34.521
What are you talking about?

17:34.556 --> 17:36.357
What else would it be?

17:38.093 --> 17:39.260
A demon.

17:39.294 --> 17:41.528
- [SHARP KNOCKING]
- Oh!

17:41.563 --> 17:43.197
I called Lem.

17:43.231 --> 17:45.532
<i>♪</i>

17:45.567 --> 17:48.502
I'm telling you, there's a demon.

17:48.536 --> 17:50.504
I've been hearing it in my house.

17:50.538 --> 17:52.573
Manfred saw it too, when
I cleansed his place.

17:52.608 --> 17:54.708
We banished it back to
the other side of the veil.

17:54.743 --> 17:56.242
Shouldn't we be getting
back to the girl?

17:56.244 --> 17:58.045
We thought we banished it,

17:58.079 --> 18:01.015
but what if that thing
is what is doing this?

18:01.038 --> 18:03.384
Demons are malevolent
beings not of this Earth.

18:03.418 --> 18:05.052
The attack on Connor

18:05.086 --> 18:07.755
was downright sloppy... Very human.

18:07.789 --> 18:11.191
Which means it's very solvable.

18:11.226 --> 18:13.360
Wait, wait, there has
to be something making me

18:13.395 --> 18:17.064
see ghosts everywhere
and Fiji see demons and...

18:17.098 --> 18:20.701
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

18:20.735 --> 18:22.803
Rev?

18:22.837 --> 18:24.571
Emilio.

18:24.606 --> 18:27.107
I'm not here as a man of God.

18:27.142 --> 18:29.310
I'm a Midnighter and a friend.

18:29.344 --> 18:32.746
I'm doing something wrong for
reasons I believe to be right,

18:32.781 --> 18:35.749
and I hope you will forgive
me, but my conscience

18:35.784 --> 18:40.120
will not allow me to
remain silent anymore.

18:40.155 --> 18:41.689
What's going on, Emilio?

18:43.658 --> 18:45.459
You need to know that
the veil between hell

18:45.493 --> 18:47.594
and Midnight is fraying.

18:47.629 --> 18:51.598
Evil energy is seeping out of
the veil, affecting all of us

18:51.633 --> 18:53.834
and bringing out the darkness in us,

18:53.868 --> 18:55.903
as well as drawing evil to Midnight.

18:55.937 --> 18:58.772
Why are we just hearing about this now?

18:58.807 --> 19:01.608
I came to you. I was
protecting my source.

19:01.643 --> 19:05.813
At my expense? There's
a demon in my house,

19:05.847 --> 19:08.449
- clawing me.
- Wait, clawing you?

19:10.452 --> 19:12.619
Are you okay?

19:12.654 --> 19:16.790
- Am I?
- I don't know.

19:16.825 --> 19:21.829
So there is a portal to
hell opening in Midnight,

19:21.863 --> 19:23.544
a girl missing

19:23.583 --> 19:27.267
and cops about to swarm
if we don't find her.

19:27.302 --> 19:33.707
<i>♪</i>

19:33.742 --> 19:36.276
Connor was attacked over there.

19:36.311 --> 19:38.645
I figured maybe I'd
get a read on something.

19:40.915 --> 19:43.183
What do you think
about what the Rev said?

19:43.218 --> 19:45.853
I'm curious who gave
him the information.

19:45.887 --> 19:50.190
I've been wondering why
I've been so hungry lately.

19:50.225 --> 19:52.192
I'm not getting any readings.

19:52.227 --> 19:54.361
<i>♪</i>

19:54.396 --> 19:55.629
I am.

19:55.663 --> 19:57.664
[INHALES]

19:57.699 --> 19:59.333
I smell blood.

19:59.367 --> 20:06.473
<i>♪</i>

20:08.000 --> 20:14.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

20:15.424 --> 20:17.191
[MOANING]

20:17.218 --> 20:18.519
You're not going anywhere.

20:18.553 --> 20:22.523
<i>♪</i>

20:22.557 --> 20:25.392
[GRUNTS]

20:25.427 --> 20:26.860
She's alive.

20:26.895 --> 20:28.929
<i>♪</i>

20:28.963 --> 20:31.698
[DOOR CLICKS OPEN]

20:31.733 --> 20:33.367
What happened?

20:33.401 --> 20:34.568
Where were you?

20:39.274 --> 20:41.675
We found the missing girl.

20:45.814 --> 20:49.550
Your father was there... with her.

20:50.885 --> 20:52.986
He found her?

21:03.498 --> 21:08.402
We think he's responsible...

21:08.436 --> 21:11.405
for Aubrey.

21:11.439 --> 21:14.975
For Tiffany. For Connor.

21:15.009 --> 21:20.447
<i>♪</i>

21:20.482 --> 21:23.717
I mean, I... We don't know for sure.

21:23.751 --> 21:26.720
He's not saying anything.

21:26.754 --> 21:29.389
- But he was there.
- Mm-hmm.

21:29.424 --> 21:33.627
<i>♪</i>

21:33.661 --> 21:35.762
[COUGHS]

21:35.797 --> 21:40.467
<i>♪</i>

21:40.502 --> 21:42.669
Why?

21:42.704 --> 21:46.473
- Why... why would he...
- I don't... I don't know.

21:46.508 --> 21:48.442
<i>♪</i>

21:48.476 --> 21:51.812
I always wondered what
drove a man to move himself,

21:51.846 --> 21:55.015
his two children, somewhere
so small and isolated.

21:55.049 --> 21:56.917
Most people wouldn't
bring their families

21:56.951 --> 22:01.989
somewhere so remote...

22:02.023 --> 22:05.826
But I imagine you loved it.

22:05.860 --> 22:08.095
We need to know for sure it's him.

22:08.129 --> 22:10.497
I found him with her.

22:10.532 --> 22:14.541
<i>♪</i>

22:14.564 --> 22:16.626
You're gonna tell me how many.

22:16.644 --> 22:19.613
How many girls have you killed?

22:26.033 --> 22:27.799
[DOOR CLICKS]

22:31.037 --> 22:33.238
You okay?

22:33.272 --> 22:37.042
You need to be honest with
me about what happened.

22:41.981 --> 22:44.015
Dad did this, didn't he?

22:44.050 --> 22:48.286
<i>♪</i>

22:48.321 --> 22:51.256
You were protecting him.

22:51.290 --> 22:55.093
Manfred and Lem found
him with the missing girl.

22:55.127 --> 22:57.224
Is she alive?

22:57.250 --> 22:59.985
She's in bad shape.

23:00.021 --> 23:03.276
But you're okay.

23:03.291 --> 23:05.479
You're safe now.

23:05.513 --> 23:08.815
I'm gonna take care of you.

23:08.850 --> 23:11.084
Where is he?

23:11.119 --> 23:13.587
The Midnighters have him now.

23:13.621 --> 23:15.989
I will drain you if you don't tell me

23:16.024 --> 23:19.059
how many people you've killed. [SNARLS]

23:19.093 --> 23:21.094
Stop, we're not
torturing Creek's father.

23:21.129 --> 23:23.096
Why not? He did worse to those victims,

23:23.131 --> 23:25.098
- to his own son.
- And he brought

23:25.133 --> 23:27.668
law enforcement here. The
man has endangered us all.

23:27.702 --> 23:30.070
Doesn't mean we can act as
judge, jury, and executioner.

23:30.104 --> 23:31.905
Oh, sure, we can. We're gonna do this

23:31.939 --> 23:35.509
The Мidnighters' way: swift and simple.

23:35.543 --> 23:37.544
There's nothing simple about this.

23:37.578 --> 23:39.613
This man should be locked away.

23:39.647 --> 23:42.616
Or we do to him what
we did to the succubus,

23:42.650 --> 23:44.618
and Zach and the other vampires.

23:44.668 --> 23:47.537
- End him.
- Maybe it's the veil.

23:47.555 --> 23:50.057
You said the veil is making
people give in to the darkness.

23:50.091 --> 23:53.093
- Maybe that's why he's...
- The veil can't make someone evil.

23:53.127 --> 23:55.028
If he gave in to the darkness,

23:55.063 --> 23:57.597
it was already there inside him.

23:57.632 --> 23:59.800
[PANTING]

23:59.834 --> 24:03.370
Creek is devastated.

24:03.404 --> 24:07.074
She needs to know why.

24:07.108 --> 24:09.743
Is that why you didn't
want me around her?

24:09.777 --> 24:13.780
'Cause you know I see the
dead and they tell me things?

24:13.815 --> 24:16.049
<i>♪</i>

24:16.084 --> 24:17.984
He's hiding something.

24:18.019 --> 24:19.786
Where are you headed?

24:19.821 --> 24:22.055
If he won't talk,
maybe his victims will.

24:22.090 --> 24:23.623
[CRASH]

24:23.658 --> 24:26.026
<i>♪</i>

24:32.100 --> 24:35.135
<i>[EERIE, MUFFLED NOISES]</i>

24:35.169 --> 24:42.442
<i>♪</i>

24:45.446 --> 24:48.548
<i>[FAINT WHISPERING, SOBBING]</i>

24:50.885 --> 24:54.488
<i>[LOUD WAILING AND SOBBING]</i>

24:54.522 --> 24:58.925
- [GROANING]
- <i>[WOMAN SCREAMING]</i>

24:58.960 --> 25:01.862
<i>[MUFFLING SOBBING]</i>

25:01.896 --> 25:04.598
<i>[WOMAN SCREAMING]</i>

25:04.632 --> 25:08.135
<i>No! No! No!</i>

25:08.169 --> 25:11.104
- [GRUNTS] <i>
- [SCREAMING]</i>

25:11.139 --> 25:18.245
<i>♪</i>

25:30.658 --> 25:31.892
<i>[SHARP RINGING MUSIC]</i>

25:31.926 --> 25:32.959
[MUFFLED SCREAM]

25:32.994 --> 25:34.895
[GUNSHOT]

25:34.929 --> 25:37.664
<i>♪</i>

25:37.698 --> 25:40.133
No, she's definitely dead.

25:40.168 --> 25:46.973
<i>♪</i>

25:47.008 --> 25:50.043
Is it him? Is he the one who hurt you?

25:50.077 --> 25:52.646
<i>♪</i>

25:52.680 --> 25:56.683
I tried to run away. But he found me.

25:56.717 --> 25:59.920
You're safe now. I promise.

25:59.954 --> 26:01.721
He had a metal pipe.

26:01.756 --> 26:04.991
He hit me with it, and I passed out.

26:05.026 --> 26:08.929
But when he came back,
I was ready for him,

26:08.963 --> 26:11.498
and I had a rock.

26:11.532 --> 26:15.001
And I hit him with it, hard,

26:15.036 --> 26:16.603
and then I just tried to get

26:16.637 --> 26:18.538
as far away from him as I could.

26:20.608 --> 26:22.242
I gave this to Aubrey.

26:22.276 --> 26:26.112
<i>♪</i>

26:26.131 --> 26:29.700
- I need to tell Creek.
- I'll go with you.

26:31.552 --> 26:33.220
- You should be in bed.
- I can't.

26:33.254 --> 26:34.921
I can't even be here in Midnight.

26:34.956 --> 26:36.857
I... I feel like I can't breathe.

26:36.891 --> 26:39.626
<i>♪</i>

26:39.660 --> 26:41.928
I know, I'm suffocating too.

26:41.963 --> 26:46.032
Dad brought us here to
hide, keep his secret.

26:46.067 --> 26:48.702
I don't feel safe here. Not anymore.

26:48.736 --> 26:51.304
I need to go.

26:51.339 --> 26:52.939
Be hard not to strangle him

26:52.974 --> 26:54.975
- with my bare hands.
- Hey, hey, hey!

26:55.009 --> 26:56.877
Creek's there. She's
been through enough.

26:56.911 --> 26:58.777
Let's not make this harder
on her than it has to be.

26:58.779 --> 27:00.814
I'll restrain myself in front of Creek.

27:00.848 --> 27:04.217
<i>♪</i>

27:04.252 --> 27:06.052
Creek?

27:06.087 --> 27:08.655
<i>♪</i>

27:08.689 --> 27:10.624
Creek?

27:10.658 --> 27:12.205
They're gone.

27:17.299 --> 27:19.070
<i>This is Creek. Leave a message.</i>

27:19.104 --> 27:21.276
Creek, it's me. Call me back.

27:21.315 --> 27:22.840
I need to know where you are. Call me.

27:22.875 --> 27:24.509
[PHONE BEEPS]

27:24.543 --> 27:28.154
I need to know. Where would Connor go?

27:28.185 --> 27:31.120
- Where would he take her?
- I don't know.

27:31.154 --> 27:32.755
I really don't.

27:32.789 --> 27:38.861
<i>♪</i>

27:40.163 --> 27:44.133
Eventually, we're gonna have to go back.

27:44.167 --> 27:46.168
Not yet.

27:46.203 --> 27:50.072
I can't face him yet.

27:50.107 --> 27:53.309
Me neither.

27:53.343 --> 27:58.080
My entire life, I've been
living with a murderer.

27:58.115 --> 28:00.216
I was too stupid to even know it.

28:02.052 --> 28:04.787
It's normal to trust family.

28:04.821 --> 28:08.357
<i>♪</i>

28:08.391 --> 28:11.427
<i>Creek never understood
why we couldn't have pets,</i>

28:11.461 --> 28:15.998
but it wasn't fair to them.

28:16.032 --> 28:20.402
It made me sick, but
Connor said that it was...

28:23.373 --> 28:24.874
Fun.

28:24.908 --> 28:27.176
<i>♪</i>

28:27.210 --> 28:29.311
We took him to doctors.

28:29.346 --> 28:31.213
They wanted to put him away.

28:31.248 --> 28:34.984
I lost my wife. I couldn't lose him too.

28:35.018 --> 28:37.186
You put our home in danger.

28:37.220 --> 28:39.388
I never meant for that to happen.

28:39.422 --> 28:42.291
I'm here because it's isolated.

28:42.325 --> 28:45.327
You all, you can protect
yourselves from him.

28:45.362 --> 28:47.196
How about the ones who couldn't, hmm?

28:47.230 --> 28:50.699
Like Aubrey, Tiffany? I
tried to keep an eye on him.

28:50.734 --> 28:54.236
I found out about Aubrey too late.

28:54.271 --> 28:57.306
When I heard about
the girl gone missing,

28:57.340 --> 28:59.809
I... I went out looking for her.

28:59.843 --> 29:01.477
I wanted to find her.

29:01.511 --> 29:04.180
He's got Creek.

29:04.214 --> 29:07.216
He wouldn't hurt her.

29:07.250 --> 29:09.718
You sure about that?

29:09.753 --> 29:13.889
<i>♪</i>

29:13.924 --> 29:15.825
I wonder if it started after Mom died.

29:15.859 --> 29:20.029
No, I bet he didn't change.

29:20.063 --> 29:23.065
I bet he was always wired different.

29:23.099 --> 29:26.235
Wired to kill innocent girls?

29:26.269 --> 29:29.371
They weren't exactly innocent.

29:29.406 --> 29:31.540
What's that supposed to mean?

29:31.575 --> 29:34.376
All I'm saying is, Aubrey
was a white supremacist.

29:34.411 --> 29:37.457
The other girl, she
was in the vampire bus.

29:37.489 --> 29:40.416
She was with the people
that tried to kill us.

29:40.450 --> 29:42.184
Why are you defending him?

29:42.219 --> 29:45.187
There is no defending what he did.

29:45.222 --> 29:47.356
He hurt you. He hurt them.

29:47.390 --> 29:49.258
[PHONE RINGING]

29:49.292 --> 29:50.901
I should just answer.

29:50.933 --> 29:52.961
- Just let it go.
- He's just gonna keep calling.

29:52.963 --> 29:54.430
Hey, Manfred...

29:54.464 --> 29:58.067
<i>♪</i>

29:58.101 --> 30:00.936
Connor, what are you doing?

30:00.971 --> 30:03.305
<i>♪</i>

30:03.340 --> 30:05.107
Connor!

30:05.141 --> 30:07.076
Connor, answer me.

30:08.311 --> 30:09.912
I don't know what happened.

30:09.946 --> 30:11.312
He must have taken the phone from her.

30:11.314 --> 30:13.249
- Connor wouldn't hurt...
- Shut up!

30:13.283 --> 30:14.654
You lied to us for years.

30:14.678 --> 30:16.317
I don't believe a
word out of your mouth.

30:16.319 --> 30:18.053
He's a killer. That's who he is.

30:18.088 --> 30:21.557
- It's his nature.
- She'll figure it out.

30:21.591 --> 30:24.426
What happens then,
when he feels cornered?

30:24.461 --> 30:31.300
<i>♪</i>

30:33.003 --> 30:34.837
Manfred, where are you going?

30:34.871 --> 30:36.972
Creek's in danger. I'm not waiting.

30:37.007 --> 30:39.140
So you're just gonna get in
your RV and start driving!

30:39.142 --> 30:40.942
- Yeah, until I find her.
- Okay, you go south.

30:40.944 --> 30:42.946
- I'll go north.
- What? They could be anywhere.

30:42.969 --> 30:44.246
It's a lot of ground to cover.

30:44.288 --> 30:45.404
Am I supposed to hope that Connor

30:45.406 --> 30:47.407
will kill a stranger but not his sister?

30:47.410 --> 30:50.085
Or just wait...

30:50.120 --> 30:51.987
just until we find her body somewhere?

30:52.022 --> 30:53.289
No.

30:53.323 --> 30:57.359
<i>♪</i>

30:57.394 --> 31:00.329
My goddess... Joe, what are you doing?

31:00.363 --> 31:04.300
[GRUNTING]

31:04.334 --> 31:11.407
<i>♪</i>

31:18.555 --> 31:20.957
I can cover more ground from above.

31:20.984 --> 31:26.055
<i>♪</i>

31:26.089 --> 31:28.257
[WINGS WHOOSHING]

31:32.095 --> 31:34.029
Was I the only one not in the loop?

31:34.064 --> 31:35.564
- Nope.
- Did not suspect that.

31:35.598 --> 31:37.333
Well, that explains a few things.

31:37.367 --> 31:39.535
- So he's an...
- Angel.

31:39.569 --> 31:42.538
<i>♪</i>

31:42.572 --> 31:44.206
Joe is an angel.

31:44.240 --> 31:46.875
<i>♪</i>

31:46.910 --> 31:51.046
Connor, it's not Dad, is it?

31:51.081 --> 31:53.215
You weren't protecting Dad.

31:53.249 --> 31:56.352
He was protecting you.

31:56.386 --> 31:59.221
Don't look at me like that.

31:59.255 --> 32:01.390
- Like what?
- Like I'm a monster.

32:01.424 --> 32:04.493
I'm no different from
everyone else in Midnight.

32:04.527 --> 32:08.497
- The Rev, once a month, he...
- He locks himself away.

32:08.531 --> 32:11.433
He makes sure not to hurt anyone else.

32:11.468 --> 32:16.572
Lem... he's a predator,
like me and Olivia.

32:16.606 --> 32:20.209
You forgive them. No, you're wrong.

32:20.243 --> 32:22.077
They don't hunt.

32:22.112 --> 32:26.015
They don't kill for the sport of it.

32:26.049 --> 32:28.083
They do it for justice,

32:28.118 --> 32:31.520
- to protect people...
- Okay, well, I'm different!

32:31.554 --> 32:34.056
<i>♪</i>

32:34.090 --> 32:36.392
I like it.

32:36.426 --> 32:41.597
<i>♪</i>

32:41.631 --> 32:44.299
Connor, we can get you help.

32:44.334 --> 32:47.036
I don't need you to fix me!

32:47.070 --> 32:49.471
Oh, oh, God.

32:49.506 --> 32:51.540
You really don't feel bad, do you?

32:51.574 --> 32:53.609
[TIRES SCREECHING]

32:53.643 --> 32:55.377
[SCREAMS]

32:55.412 --> 32:56.545
[HORN BLARES]

32:56.579 --> 32:58.747
Stop the car right now!

32:58.782 --> 33:00.649
I'm not going back.
Don't try and stop me.

33:00.683 --> 33:02.451
Connor, you're gonna get us killed!

33:02.485 --> 33:05.954
<i>♪</i>

33:05.989 --> 33:07.456
[ENERGY WHOOSHES]

33:07.490 --> 33:10.626
[BOTH GASP]

33:10.660 --> 33:13.762
<i>♪</i>

33:13.797 --> 33:15.631
- Creek, you all right?
- [CAR DOOR SLAMS]

33:15.665 --> 33:17.633
It was him. He did it all.

33:17.667 --> 33:20.669
- We know.
- [GASPING]

33:20.703 --> 33:24.139
- Connor, you need to stop.
- He doesn't care.

33:24.174 --> 33:26.575
He doesn't wanna change.
He killed them all!

33:26.609 --> 33:29.078
You're okay. You're safe now.

33:29.112 --> 33:31.413
[PANTING]

33:31.448 --> 33:38.554
<i>♪</i>

33:42.025 --> 33:46.428
<i>[GRITTY ROCK MUSIC]</i>

33:46.463 --> 33:48.130
[SHARP SNAP]

34:01.396 --> 34:04.977
<i>[GENTLE MUSIC]</i>

34:05.012 --> 34:10.783
<i>♪</i>

34:10.818 --> 34:17.143
<i>♪ In the black depth of my heart ♪</i>

34:17.166 --> 34:23.295
<i>♪ We'll await our deaths ♪</i>

34:23.330 --> 34:29.969
<i>♪ And the time has just begun ♪</i>

34:30.003 --> 34:36.742
<i>♪ I hear a call at night ♪</i>

34:36.777 --> 34:39.745
<i>[WOMAN SINGING INDISTINCTLY]</i>

34:39.780 --> 34:46.819
<i>♪</i>

34:49.306 --> 34:54.610
<i>♪</i>

34:54.614 --> 34:56.982
There's no scar.

34:57.013 --> 35:00.600
Got a trick or two up my sleeve.

35:00.634 --> 35:02.602
You gonna be okay?

35:02.636 --> 35:04.337
Yeah. [SIGHS]

35:06.198 --> 35:09.008
Thanks to you.

35:09.042 --> 35:11.611
So you know, the boy who hurt you,

35:11.645 --> 35:14.614
he'll never hurt anyone again.

35:14.648 --> 35:16.449
We made sure of that.

35:18.685 --> 35:21.621
You know what people in Davy think.

35:21.655 --> 35:23.623
If they heard what happened here...

35:23.657 --> 35:25.491
They'd burn this place to the ground.

35:27.895 --> 35:30.396
I won't lie.

35:30.430 --> 35:32.632
I'll...

35:32.666 --> 35:37.370
I'll tell 'em that I got hurt

35:37.404 --> 35:40.806
and an awfully nice group
of Midnighters found me.

35:43.777 --> 35:47.713
And they took care of me.

35:47.748 --> 35:49.849
[CAR APPROACHING]

35:49.883 --> 35:51.817
That's my mom.

35:53.120 --> 36:00.059
<i>♪</i>

36:01.562 --> 36:03.529
You take care.

36:05.098 --> 36:06.566
Thanks.

36:15.542 --> 36:18.744
You did a good thing, Fiji.

36:18.779 --> 36:25.151
One good thing in an
otherwise awful, awful day.

36:29.122 --> 36:32.592
I feel like Midnight'll
never be okay again.

36:32.626 --> 36:39.031
<i>♪</i>

36:40.100 --> 36:42.101
[DOOR CLANKS]

36:43.737 --> 36:50.776
<i>♪</i>

36:54.915 --> 36:56.916
Connor's gone.

36:56.950 --> 36:59.752
<i>♪</i>

36:59.786 --> 37:01.420
Can I explain?

37:01.455 --> 37:03.222
Explain what?

37:03.257 --> 37:07.126
How you made me feel like I
had to take care of Connor?

37:07.160 --> 37:10.997
Like I had to watch over him?

37:11.031 --> 37:14.767
You made me complicit in when he did.

37:14.801 --> 37:16.435
I'm so sorry.

37:16.470 --> 37:19.939
<i>♪</i>

37:19.973 --> 37:22.842
Please...

37:22.876 --> 37:25.911
You're all I have left.

37:25.946 --> 37:28.681
You don't have me.

37:28.715 --> 37:31.117
You chose to be a father to Connor

37:31.151 --> 37:35.521
and to protect all of the
evil things that he did.

37:35.555 --> 37:37.156
- He was my son.
- What about all of

37:37.190 --> 37:39.091
the girls that he killed?

37:39.126 --> 37:41.827
There are parents
mourning because of him,

37:41.862 --> 37:43.796
and you protected him.

37:43.830 --> 37:46.632
It didn't matter that other
people's children died.

37:48.969 --> 37:51.103
We're all that's left.

37:51.138 --> 37:53.139
<i>♪</i>

37:53.173 --> 37:55.708
Please.

37:55.742 --> 37:57.977
I'm your dad.

37:58.011 --> 38:01.847
No, you were his father.

38:01.882 --> 38:04.016
You didn't think about me.

38:04.051 --> 38:07.219
<i>♪</i>

38:07.254 --> 38:09.789
So this is it.

38:09.823 --> 38:13.159
I don't ever want to see you again.

38:13.193 --> 38:15.161
I can't.

38:15.195 --> 38:22.268
<i>♪</i>

38:25.038 --> 38:26.739
<i>Fire destroys.</i>

38:26.773 --> 38:28.908
[FLAMES CRACKLING]

38:28.942 --> 38:31.877
<i>It also cleanses.</i>

38:31.912 --> 38:34.313
We honor the spirits

38:34.348 --> 38:37.817
that were torn from this life.

38:37.851 --> 38:42.521
Let us cleanse the pain...

38:42.556 --> 38:44.824
<i>♪</i>

38:44.858 --> 38:48.761
The suffering they experienced.

38:48.795 --> 38:54.200
From this hate, let love be found.

38:54.234 --> 38:59.705
And from this violence,
let peace emerge.

38:59.740 --> 39:01.707
Farewell...

39:01.742 --> 39:03.042
<i>♪</i>

39:03.076 --> 39:04.877
And blessed be.

39:04.911 --> 39:06.912
<i>♪</i>

39:06.947 --> 39:10.216
<i>♪ And when I sleep ♪</i>

39:10.250 --> 39:13.719
<i>♪</i>

39:13.754 --> 39:17.123
<i>♪ And if I woke ♪</i>

39:17.157 --> 39:20.593
<i>♪</i>

39:20.619 --> 39:24.562
<i>♪ And when I run away ♪</i>

39:24.601 --> 39:26.732
Fiji said it would make you feel better.

39:26.767 --> 39:29.039
<i>♪ Hold me in your arms ♪</i>

39:29.070 --> 39:32.371
Unless it'll help me
forget what happened.

39:32.406 --> 39:34.373
<i>♪</i>

39:34.408 --> 39:37.743
<i>♪ Don't let go</i>

39:37.778 --> 39:39.979
I'm sorry.

39:40.013 --> 39:43.215
<i>♪ Hold me in your arms ♪</i>

39:43.250 --> 39:47.119
[SOBBING]

39:47.154 --> 39:53.626
<i>♪ And when I run away ♪</i>

39:53.660 --> 39:58.664
<i>♪ Hold me in your arms ♪</i>

39:58.698 --> 40:05.805
<i>♪</i>

40:20.320 --> 40:23.322
Well...

40:23.356 --> 40:26.292
You must be angry with me.

40:26.326 --> 40:30.429
No, I'm not.

40:30.464 --> 40:33.132
If you hadn't done what you did,

40:33.166 --> 40:34.985
I might not have gone after Creek.

40:35.007 --> 40:36.660
I think you would have.

40:36.680 --> 40:40.039
Maybe...

40:40.073 --> 40:42.808
But I used my light to save her,

40:42.843 --> 40:44.910
which means they will be coming for me.

40:49.983 --> 40:53.319
I should call Chuy and tell him.

40:53.353 --> 40:56.055
Thank you, Joe.

40:56.089 --> 41:00.359
If you need anything, we're here.

41:00.393 --> 41:07.299
<i>♪</i>

41:14.074 --> 41:18.010
<i>You've reached Chuy. Leave me a message.</i>

41:18.044 --> 41:20.012
Chuy, it's me.

41:20.046 --> 41:22.882
<i>♪</i>

41:22.916 --> 41:24.850
You need to know that
it's not safe for you

41:24.885 --> 41:28.478
in Midnight anymore.

41:28.510 --> 41:31.991
If they find out who
you are, they'll kill me,

41:32.025 --> 41:34.541
and they will exterminate you,

41:34.566 --> 41:37.901
so please, stay away.

41:40.632 --> 41:43.467
War is coming here,

41:43.494 --> 41:45.094
and I need to stay and fight it.

41:45.124 --> 41:47.373
<i>♪</i>

